# 🧠 Concept 2: Data Replication Strategies

🔥 One of the most important distributed-system concepts.

---

## First Understand Why Replication Exists

Suppose you have:

```text
One Database Server
```

If it crashes:

❌ System down

---

## Solution

Create copies.

```text
Primary
 ↓
Replica 1
 ↓
Replica 2
```

---

# Types of Replication

---

## 1. Synchronous Replication

Write succeeds only when replicas update.

### Advantage

✔ Strong consistency

### Disadvantage

❌ Higher latency

---

## 2. Asynchronous Replication

Primary responds immediately.

Replicas update later.

### Advantage

✔ Faster

### Disadvantage

❌ Temporary inconsistency

---

## Real-World Analogy

Class Notes 📖

Synchronous:

Everyone updates notes immediately.

Asynchronous:

Some students copy notes later.

---

## Interview Question

**Q: Why do many large systems use asynchronous replication?**

👉 Because it improves performance and availability.

---

## Memory Trick

```text
Sync = Safe but Slow

Async = Fast but Delayed
```

---

# ⚙️ Concept 3: Computational Storage

🔥 Emerging architecture concept.

---

## Traditional Storage

Storage only stores data.

CPU performs computation.

```text
Storage
 ↓
Move Data
 ↓
CPU
```

---

## Problem

Huge data movement.

---

## Solution

Perform computation inside storage devices.

---

## Example

Instead of moving:

```text
10 TB log file
```

to CPU,

Storage performs:

```text
Filtering
Searching
Aggregation
```

internally.

---

## Real-World Analogy

Instead of bringing all books home to search for one page:

👉 Search inside library.

---

## Benefits

✔ Lower latency

✔ Lower bandwidth usage

✔ Better energy efficiency

---

## Interview Question

**Q: Why computational storage is attractive?**

👉 Because moving data is often more expensive than processing it.

---

## Memory Trick

```text
Move Compute

Not Data
```

---

# ⚙️ Concept 4: Agentic RAG Systems

🔥 One of the hottest AI architecture topics.

---

## Recall RAG

RAG:

```text
Retrieve
 ↓
Generate
```

---

## Traditional RAG

User asks question.

System retrieves information.

LLM answers.

---

## Agentic RAG

Adds reasoning and planning.

Agent can:

✔ Decide what to search

✔ Search multiple sources

✔ Verify results

✔ Perform tool calls

✔ Generate final answer

---

## Real-World Analogy

Student solving assignment.

Instead of reading one book:

👉 searches multiple references

👉 verifies facts

👉 combines information

---

## Workflow

```text
Question
 ↓
Plan
 ↓
Retrieve
 ↓
Evaluate
 ↓
Generate
```

---

## Why Important?

Improves:

✔ accuracy

✔ reasoning

✔ reliability

---

## Interview Question

**Q: Difference between RAG and Agentic RAG?**

👉 Agentic RAG adds planning, reasoning, and tool usage before generating answers.

---

## Memory Trick

```text
RAG = Search + Answer

Agentic RAG = Think + Search + Answer
```

---

